#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.145"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.145:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.145:0.2"
msgid "15. Ābhāvagga"
msgstr "15. Brightness"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.145:0.3"
msgid "145. Pajjotasutta"
msgstr "145. Lamps"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.145:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, pajjotā."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four lamps."

msgctxt "an4.145:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "an4.145:1.3"
msgid "Candapajjoto, sūriyapajjoto, aggipajjoto, paññāpajjoto—"
msgstr "The lamps of the moon, sun, fire, and wisdom."

msgctxt "an4.145:1.4"
msgid "ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro pajjotā."
msgstr "These are the four lamps."

msgctxt "an4.145:1.5"
msgid "Etadaggaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ catunnaṃ pajjotānaṃ yadidaṃ paññāpajjoto”ti."
msgstr "The best of these four lamps is the lamp of wisdom.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.145:1.6"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
